## PlantUML Patterns

### Sequence Diagram

```plantuml
@startuml
!theme plain

actor User
participant "Web App" as Web
participant "API Server" as API
database "Database" as DB

title User Authentication Flow

== Login ==
User -> Web: Enter credentials
Web -> API: POST /auth/login
API -> DB: Query user
DB --> API: User record

alt Valid credentials
  API --> Web: JWT token
  Web --> User: Redirect to dashboard
else Invalid
  API --> Web: 401 Unauthorized
  Web --> User: Show error
end

@enduml
```

### Component Diagram

```plantuml
@startuml
!theme plain

package "API Server" {
  [Auth Controller] as AuthCtrl
  [User Controller] as UserCtrl
  [Auth Service] as AuthSvc
  [User Service] as UserSvc
  [User Repository] as UserRepo
}

database "PostgreSQL" as DB

AuthCtrl --> AuthSvc
UserCtrl --> UserSvc
AuthSvc --> UserRepo
UserSvc --> UserRepo
UserRepo --> DB

@enduml
```

### Key PlantUML Syntax

**Participants**: `actor`, `participant`, `boundary`, `control`, `entity`, `database`, `queue`

**Arrows**:
- `->` solid
- `-->` dotted
- `->>` thin
- `<->` bidirectional

**Control flow**:
- `alt/else/end` — conditional
- `opt/end` — optional
- `loop/end` — repetition
- `par/end` — parallel
- `break/end` — exit early

**Sections**: `== Section Name ==`

**Notes**: `note left of X: text`, `note over X,Y: text`

