.spec/e2e-coordinator-config-schema.md:143:`peer-listener` is for physical-device setups where peers expose a device-side TCP listener and the Mac runner connects through the peer `connection` block, usually with `iproxy`.
.spec/e2e-coordinator-config-schema.md:145:### `artifacts`
.spec/e2e-coordinator-config-schema.md:151:| `root` | path template | yes | Run artifact root. Supports `${sessionId}` and `${profileName}`. |
.spec/e2e-coordinator-config-schema.md:152:| `keepSuccessfulRuns` | bool | no | Whether successful run artifacts are preserved. Default: `true`. |
.spec/e2e-coordinator-config-schema.md:153:| `writeResolvedConfig` | bool | no | Write fully resolved config into artifacts. Default: `true`. |
.spec/e2e-coordinator-config-schema.md:217:| `coordinatorHost` | string | no | Peer-specific advertised coordinator host for `websocket` transport. |
.spec/e2e-coordinator-config-schema.md:218:| `connection` | object | required when `coordinator.transport=peer-listener` | Peer listener connection and optional proxy settings. |
.spec/e2e-coordinator-config-schema.md:224:| `artifacts` | object | no | Peer-specific artifact overrides. |
.spec/e2e-coordinator-config-schema.md:338:### `connection`
