   246	### Peer-Listener Transport
   247
   248	Use `coordinator.transport: peer-listener` when physical iOS peers cannot reach a Mac-hosted WebSocket coordinator directly. In this mode each UI test peer starts a device-side TCP listener, the Mac runner starts `iproxy` for each connected device, and the Mac-side coordinator connects to every peer through the forwarded localhost ports.
   249
   250	Consumer UI tests should import `IOSE2EPeerClient` and use `UITestE2EClient.fromEnvironment()`. Do not import `IOSE2ECoordinatorCore` from product tests just to inspect peer names; use `client.environment.peerNameValue` for project scenario branching.
   251
   252	```yaml
   253	coordinator:
   254	  transport: peer-listener
